photo.title: One Sick Moon

description._content:
The full moon rise today over San Francisco's Coit Tower was quite a thrill. I think I caught bug that has been passing around an i'm sure tomorrow will be hell to pay when I cough like crazy. 

Anyways, tonight's chasing the moon was a thrill. We parked at a good spot where cars come and go, but when the moon rose above the horizon, guess what, nothing. 

It wasn't until a lot of moving, relocating and trial and error that we found the spot. There was a small alley of opportunity and within a few minutes, the opportunity was gone. 

Fighting a cold while carrying a bunch of equipment isn't my idea of fun, but the results made it worth while. 

Time to rest up!

photo.title: "Falling Sky"

description._content:
Wow! There was so much drama in Saturday's sunset! As an incredibly fiery orange sun was setting, amazingly unstable and lightning-filled clouds added more spectacle to the show. The awesome falling sky left the Coit Tower like a giant flaming candle over The City. Super!

A magnificent Saturday evening show!

#sanfrancisco  
#sunset  
#alwayssf  

— in San Francisco, California.﻿

photo.title: Taking Chances

description._content: So Wilson and I took chances to see this beautiful moonrise tonight. We knew that it will be only a few percentage to see the moon aligned on the Coit Tower due to the clouds covering it after it rose by the hills. After waiting for 20 mins as the moon rose. We decided to call it a day. Suddenly, on our way back to our cars. We saw some hopes for the moon will soon be visible behind those clouds. We then started running to couple of streets away from where the plan was and following the other photographers. Then bayum! We got it!
